The paper discusses techniques to improve the generalization of deep representations learned on small labeled datasets, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on few-shot learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that deals with learning from small amounts of labeled data. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
